d social justice, equal opportunities and institutional racism. It will appeal to students, researchers and practitioners in education, social policy, sociology and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aInclusive educationzGreat Britain. 0aProblem childrenxBehavior modificationzGreat Britain. 0aSchool disciplinezGreat Britain. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311119643540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447317494423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447317494/original  a978-3-11-119643-5  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles